# .cursorignore — approved-context boundary for the diffusers assistant
# Principle: the agent reasons only from current, canonical, convention-
# following code. If we wouldn't hand it to a new hire as a reference,
# the agent doesn't see it either.

# --- Convention hazards: code that teaches the wrong patterns ---
examples/research_projects/     # frozen research code, explicitly unmaintained
examples/community/             # community pipelines — not held to core conventions
**/deprecated/                  # kept for backwards compat, not a pattern source

# --- Noise: wastes context window, adds no signal ---
docs/source/_build/
*.ipynb                         # notebooks: stale API usage, huge token cost
benchmarks/

# --- Binary / generated artifacts ---
*.safetensors
*.bin
*.onnx
*.png
*.gif

# --- Customer-translation section (empty here, populated in a real engagement) ---
# .env*
# **/credentials/
# **/fixtures/customer_data/
# vendor/